name: John Gustafson
description: John has nearly 25 years of experience advising investors and companies in preparing for, and successfully closing, strategic transactions - ranging from mergers and acquisitions (M&A), capital raising, asset acquisitions, and asset diversitures. He currently serves as the founder and president of Skyline Advisors, a boutique investment bank focused on serving the needs of investors, family-owned businesses, high growth companies, and lower middle market firms (enterprise values of $10 million to $250 million).Previously with CBS Commercial, John transferred his license to BHHS Ambassador Real Estate in October 2018.  John's real estate activities center on assisting families, investors, and companies with the purchase, sale, or leasing of commercial and investment properties.  Typically, his real estate work is part of a client's broader strategic plan.A fourth generation Nebraskan, John was raised in West Point, Nebraska and graduated with an accounting degree from the University of Nebraska - Lincoln. After college, he earned the Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) designation from the CFA Institute and his MBA from the Kellogg Graduate School at Northwestern University.  John began his career with two early stage venture capital funds focused on making investments in high growth technology, healthcare and manufacturing companies.  Later, he managed a family office / holding company with a broad portfolio of wholly-owned subsidiaries and investments in real estate, banking, and health care technology. As part of these activities, John served as the CEO of various portfolio companies, including an international firm that was acquired by a publicly-traded company. He founded Skyline Advisors in 2005 and teamed up with CFO Systems, a provider of interim and timeshare Chief Financial Officers and Controllers, in 2014 to oversee their Corporate Development practice.John was named to M&A Advisor’s 2014 national “40 Under 40” list the Dealmaker category. He is a member of the CFA Institute, the Association for Corporate Growth (ACG), and the advisory board for the Finance Department at the University of Nebraska - Lincoln.John's wife, Deb, is a residential real estate agent with BHHS Ambassador Real Estate leading the Deb Gustafson Group. John and Deb have three children and enjoy travelling, college football, and keeping up with kids’ activities.

name: Teresa Kelley
description: Specialties: Buyer's Agent, Listing Agent, Short-Sale, ConsultingFor as long as I can remember I wanted to be a Realtor and through my life I have been pulled into this line of work.  When I was young my mother and I didn't have much extra money to go do things so we went to a lot of open houses. I loved imagining living in them and what room would be mine but I knew we wouldn't be able to afford them.  That didn't matter to me I just loved going through them. Even to this day my mom and I still love driving around looking at homes.Patrick and I had our first child at a young age.  My dreams of being a successful Realtor were put on hold for a while.  Now we have 5 wonderful children and I understand the many blessings as well as the hardships that come along with motherhood.  My faith in Realtors was initially strained while looking for our first home, a far from perfect fixer-upper. It was difficult finding a Realtor to help us look for that specific home so I ended up finding it myself.Shortly before moving in to our second home I finally decided to get my license.  It was after a series of disappointments working with 5 different Realtors while trying to purchase it.  Although many of my troubles were avoidable I learned the hard way what it takes to represent your clients and how even a few oversights or simply dragging your feet can cost the clients a tremendous amount.  I decided that I could easily do what these Realtors chose not to do and made a commitment to myself to always treat my clients the way they deserve to be treated and to be an example of what a true Realtor should be.I have built and plan to build many more long lasting friendships through my business and to help people buy and sell homes!

name: Joel Johnson
description: One of the biggest decisions a person will make is buying a home. While it is certainly an exciting time, this process can also be a time of stress. My passion is helping clients maximize the joy and excitement of home ownership and to mitigate those items that might create stress during this process.If you are selling your home, allow me to provide and explain facts and numbers to help you price your home correctly and attract prospective buyers. Work with me to present your home in “its” best light. My goal is to create as many showings of your home as quickly as I can. As part of this process, I will call you to schedule each showing to ensure it works with your schedule. Post showing, I will contact the showing agent as soon as possible for feedback about the showing. This way, we get the feedback from the agent that is showing houses in your home’s price range and also get the feedback of their buyer on how your home compares. I will provide straightforward, open and timely communication tailored around your expectations, with a weekly summary and updates on showings and the feedback we have received. We will discuss and plan future open houses and other decisions regarding your home weekly.At The Metro Pros, our team works together to determine correct pricing, staging suggestions, and of course marketing strategies, so that hundreds more potential buyers in our area will see your home.I place a high value on every single relationship I make with all my clients, other agents, lenders and everyone I have the privilege of working with.
